# Action Items Standard Format

## Purpose
Standardize action items across all CRM files to enable automatic extraction, tracking, and prioritization.

## Where Action Items Belong

**Action items should ONLY exist in:**
- `/active_leads/` - For potential opportunities in the pipeline
- `/projects/` - For confirmed work and active engagements

**Action items should NEVER exist in:**
- `/people/` - People files document relationships, not tasks. If you need to do something involving a person, create or reference a lead/project file instead.

**Why this separation?**
- **People files** are permanent relationship records (who they are, how you met, interactions)
- **Leads/Projects** are temporary work items that get archived when complete
- This keeps your active task list focused and prevents stale action items from cluttering people files

## Standard Format

**REQUIRED FORMAT** - All action items MUST follow this exact structure:

```markdown
- [ ] **PRIORITY:** Task description *(added YYYY-MM-DD)*
```

### Priority Levels (REQUIRED)
- `**URGENT:**` - Within 24 hours
- `**HIGH:**` - Within week
- `**MEDIUM:**` - Default priority (still must be explicit)
- `**LOW:**` - When time permits

### Date Tag (REQUIRED)
- `*(added YYYY-MM-DD)*` - When item was created
- `*(moved from YYYY-MM-DD)*` - When item was moved from another file

### Complete Examples
```markdown
- [ ] **URGENT:** Respond to client's email about partnership proposal *(added 2025-11-13)*
- [ ] **HIGH:** Follow up on coffee meeting from Nov 10 *(added 2025-11-13)*
- [ ] **MEDIUM:** Schedule Q1 2026 check-in call *(added 2025-11-08)*
- [ ] **LOW:** Research competitor pricing *(added 2025-11-12)*
- [ ] **HIGH:** Task moved from last week *(moved from 2025-11-06)*
```

### ‚ùå INVALID FORMATS (Do Not Use)
```markdown
- [ ] Task without priority or date
- [ ] Task with date only *(added 2025-11-13)*
- [ ] **HIGH:** Task with priority only
- [ ] üî¥ Task with emoji instead of text priority *(added 2025-11-13)*
- [ ] URGENT: Task with unbolded priority *(added 2025-11-13)*
```

