## Priority Levels

### üî¥ URGENT (Priority 1)
- Requires immediate attention (within 24 hours)
- Blocking other work
- Has external deadline
- Client-facing and time-sensitive

**Keywords:** URGENT, ASAP, CRITICAL, BLOCKER

### üü° HIGH (Priority 2)
- Important but not immediate (within week)
- Key business relationships
- Revenue-generating activities
- Strategic opportunities

**Keywords:** HIGH, IMPORTANT, PRIORITY

### üü¢ MEDIUM (Priority 3)
- Standard work items
- Regular follow-ups
- General maintenance tasks
- Default priority level

**Keyword REQUIRED:** `**MEDIUM:**` (must be explicit, no defaults)

### ‚ö™ LOW (Priority 4)
- Nice to have
- Can be deferred
- Low impact if delayed
- Background tasks

**Keywords:** LOW, NICE-TO-HAVE, OPTIONAL, WHEN-TIME-PERMITS

