## Best Practices

### DO ‚úÖ
- [ ] **Be specific:** "Call John about Q1 project pricing" not "Follow up with John"
- [ ] **ALWAYS add priority:** Use `**URGENT:**`, `**HIGH:**`, `**MEDIUM:**`, or `**LOW:**`
- [ ] **ALWAYS add date:** Include `*(added YYYY-MM-DD)*` when creating
- [ ] **One action per line:** Don't combine multiple actions
- [ ] **Use consistent sections:** Always place under `## Action Items` heading
- [ ] **Link references:** Use `[file](mdc:path/to/file.md)` for task context files
- [ ] **Follow exact format:** `- [ ] **PRIORITY:** Task *(added YYYY-MM-DD)*`
- [ ] **Place in correct files:** ONLY in `/active_leads/` or `/projects/` files, NEVER in `/people/` files

### DON'T ‚ùå
- [ ] ~~Vague actions~~ ‚Üí "Do the thing" (too vague)
- [ ] ~~Multiple actions~~ ‚Üí "Call John and email Sarah and book meeting" (split these)
- [ ] ~~No context~~ ‚Üí Items without enough detail to execute
- [ ] ~~Scattered placement~~ ‚Üí Action items placed randomly in file
- [ ] ~~Missing priority~~ ‚Üí Every action item MUST have a priority marker
- [ ] ~~Missing date~~ ‚Üí Every action item MUST have a date tag
- [ ] ~~Emoji priorities~~ ‚Üí Use text (`**URGENT:**`) not emoji (üî¥)
- [ ] ~~Unbolded priorities~~ ‚Üí Must be `**URGENT:**` not `URGENT:`
- [ ] ~~Action items in people files~~ ‚Üí People files are for relationship documentation, not tasks

